example.para: The following code fragment helps to show the meaning of the LookupTablesRow property. If the lutUid value is the GUID of a lookup table and LookupTableTrees[6] is a valid LookupTableTreesRow, then lutUidFromTreeNode gets the same GUID value. LookupTableWS is an arbitrary name for a reference to the LookupTable Web service.

Docs.summary: Specifies the duration value in a lookup table of the Duration type.

remarks.para: The duration value is in tenths of a minute. For example, if the working day is eight hours, the duration value for one working day is 4800 (8 hours x 60 minutes/hour x 10 tenths/minute). If the LT_VALUE_DUR is specified, the must also be specified.
If the lookup table is not a Duration type, then the LT_VALUE_DUR property is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::String ^ LT_VALUE_FULL { System::String ^ get(); void set(System::String ^ value); };
member this.LT_VALUE_FULL : string with get, set

Docs.summary: Shows the full value of a multilevel lookup table node, including the parent values with separator characters.

remarks.para: For example, if the parent node value of a lookup table of type Text is England, the child value is Sussex, and the separator character is a period ("^"), the full value of the child node is England^Sussex.
